definition.value: A member of the cadinene family of sesquiterpenes in which the double bonds are located at the 4-4a and 7-8 positions, and in which the isopropyl group at position 1 is cis to the hydrogen at the adjacent bridgehead carbon (the 1S,8aR-enantiomer).
A glycosyl glycoside derivative consisting of consisting of beta-D-glucosamine and alpha-D-glucopyranose residues joined by a (1->1) glycosidic bond.
A glycosylgalactose consisting of alpha-D-mannopyranose and D-galactopyranose residues joined in sequence by a (1->6) glycosidic bond.
